# Grid System & Layout Rules

This project uses a **responsive card-based grid system** with TailwindCSS and DaisyUI components.

## Core Grid Structure

The main dashboard grid is defined in [Dashboard.tsx](mdc:src/components/Dashboard.tsx):

```tsx
<main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-8">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
    {children}
  </div>
</main>
```

### Grid Layout Rules

- **Responsive Design**: Always use `grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3` for main dashboard
  - 1 column on mobile and tablet (default)
  - 3 columns on large screens (`lg:` breakpoint)
- **Consistent Spacing**: Use `gap-6` between grid items
- **Container Pattern**: Wrap grid in `container mx-auto px-6 py-8`

## WidgetCard Component

All dashboard widgets MUST be wrapped in [WidgetCard](mdc:src/widgets/WidgetCard.tsx):

```tsx
<WidgetCard title="Widget Name" client:load>
  <YourWidget client:only="preact" />
</WidgetCard>
```

### WidgetCard Specifications

- **Square Aspect**: Uses `aspect-square` class for consistent sizing
- **Card Structure**: Built on DaisyUI `card bg-base-100 shadow-lg`
- **Flexible Content**: Content area has `flex-1 overflow-y-auto` for scrollable content
- **Title Styling**: Consistent `card-title text-lg font-semibold mb-3`

## Widget Development Guidelines

### New Widget Creation

When creating new widgets:

1. **Create in `/src/widgets/{category}/` directory**
2. **Export widget component at top of file** (memory preference)
3. **Use WidgetCard wrapper** in [index.astro](mdc:src/pages/index.astro)
4. **Follow TypeScript typing patterns**

### Widget Structure Example

```tsx
// src/widgets/new-tool/NewToolWidget.tsx
import type { ComponentChildren } from "preact";

export const NewToolWidget = () => {
  return (
    <div class="h-full flex flex-col space-y-4">
      {/* Widget content */}
    </div>
  );
};
```

### Integration in Dashboard

Add to [index.astro](mdc:src/pages/index.astro):

```tsx
<WidgetCard title="New Tool" client:load>
  <NewToolWidget client:only="preact" />
</WidgetCard>
```

## Responsive Breakpoints

Follow TailwindCSS conventions:
- **Default (mobile)**: `grid-cols-1`
- **Large screens**: `lg:grid-cols-3` (1024px+)
- **Spacing**: Consistent `gap-6` across all breakpoints

